Emma RICE, as Owner of THE Scow PHILIP R. and Alex Terro, Master of Said Scow, Libelants-Appellees, v. THE Tug GOODWIN NO. 14, Her Engines, etc., Claimant-Appellant. No. 128. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 5, 1931. Macklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Park, Mattison & Lynch, of New York City (Anthony Y. Lynch, Jr., and John K. Hartley, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
